# Samba Installation and HDD Preparation

## Step 1: Update system packages
```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
Step 2: Install required packages
exFAT support (for some drives), NTFS support, and Samba itself
bash
Copy code
sudo apt install exfat-utils exfat-fuse ntfs-3g samba samba-common-bin -y
Step 3: Connect external HDD to Raspberry Pi
After plugging in, check available devices
bash
Copy code
lsblk
Example output:
sda 465.8G
└─sda2 465.7G
Note down your device (e.g. /dev/sda2)
yaml
Copy code

---

## Step 4: Unmount drive (if auto-mounted)
```bash
sudo umount /dev/sda2
Step 5: Prepare for mounting
Do NOT mount permanently yet (covered in directory-structure.md)
Just confirm you can mount manually
bash
Copy code
sudo mkdir -p /mnt/myhdd
sudo mount /dev/sda2 /mnt/myhdd
Verify
bash
Copy code
ls /mnt/myhdd
Step 6: Install check (verify Samba installed)
bash
Copy code
smbd --version
Output should show installed Samba version.




